&gt; I think it varies depending on who you ask as well as what they  have 
&gt; personally experienced. As an example, some people believe in  angels and demons 
&gt; others do not. Therefor some may get messages that  correspond to their own 
&gt; beliefs as well as the beliefs of those who  are speaking.
&gt; 
&gt; Almost every person who does this eventually  develops a theory that may 
&gt; change over time based on what they  experience and what their beliefs are. 
&gt; Then there are those who  remain undecided or have doubts.
&gt; 
&gt; As for me I look at it as  purely educational, a learning experience. Ive 
&gt; met many people I  never knew existed. Ive researched topics I&#39;d never even 
&gt; considered.  Ive gotten messages and images that are awe inspiring and many  
&gt; interesting concepts to ponder and explore.
&gt; 
&gt; There are many  glimpses of truth, as well as momentary proof along the way 
&gt; that  lead me to develop my own theory and eventually you will develop  
&gt; your own too. This research is fascinating and can be quite mind  blowing.
&gt; 
&gt; I dont worry what anyone else thinks. I have no need  to prove anything to 
&gt; anyone else. They can do that for themselves. I  always say honesty is the 
&gt; best policy and if you are honest with  yourself and others the only ones who 
&gt; object are those who&#39;s lies  arent tolerated. So just look for the truth 
&gt; yourself and dont let me  or anyone else tell you what that is. 
&gt; 
&gt; It&#39;s a great journey  and your path is your own!
&gt; 
&gt; Misty
